			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well I hate to say use AA to help fix mage pet problems but honestly its going to be the best way to go.
<br />

<br />
Reasons why?  Well if you do it as a scroll its either going to be GoD based (boo) and no drop or something really hard to get.  AA have to be earned by raiding mages and by exp mages alike.  Therefore, this prevents a lvl 65 'bazaar mage' having the same powerful pet that a lvl 65 with 300 aa has.
<br />

<br />
Ok now for the ideas.  
<br />

<br />
lvl 61+ pet costing 9-15AA to purchase.  recast of say a few seconds.  upgrade to rage of zomm called rage of tallon (or something else =P).  
<br />

<br />
Rage of Tallon works like this.  When you cast it, you have to have a mob targetted.  Rage of Tallon will cause any other pet you have to immediately poof and it will attack your target.  It would have earthish HPs and mitigate about the same.  RoT procs a 55% slow on whatever it is fighting about once every 12 seconds.  spell proc has a -50 resist adjust and lasts 2 ticks (12 seconds).  The pet would hit for approx 50 hps and could be buffed if the mage so chose (bo5, DS).  When the mob dies, the pet poofs.  Unless the mage has aggro on another mob, and the RoT pet will run over to that mob and melee.
<br />

<br />
RoT proc will not stack with any form of slow.  RoT cannot wield any weapons or wear any armor.  it can be buffed and thats it.
<br />

<br />
What this pet does?
<br />

<br />
Effectively gives mages a form of crowd control by pet parking.  We can only hold off one add, but this is not something that is new to mages.  Would just be new to the 61+ crowd.
<br />

<br />
Lowers mages overall DPS a bit, however does give groups a reason to think about adding us.
<br />

<br />
Doesn't use mana so we don't have to spend massive amounts of mana cast a pet and we can use that extra mana to nuke.
<br />

<br />
Gives mages a unique ability once again.
<br />

<br />
What this pet doesnt?
<br />

<br />
Doesn't give us a castable version of the  'slow' spell or any effective way to be uber and hold off 3-4 adds.
<br />

<br />
Doesn't give great DPS for soloing.  It will be decent DPS but nothing like the other 61+ dps pets.
<br />

<br />
Doesn't step on any other classes toes.  We won't be looked for as a 'slower', but rather DPS with utility.
<br />

<br />
please make constructive comments <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />  I thought about this today as our exp group kept getting 1 addtl add and no one to offtank it (except my airpet that kept dying).  also if you can think of any real exploits for this, lets hear it so we can modify the idea, if people like the idea that is<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=182653"> Wrathen's Stuff</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
