				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm pretty sure everyone in the game would consider a mage slowing to be an exploit :p
<br />

<br />
I actually rather like this idea. I don't think it will ever be implimented, but I really do like it. We might be taken in a group rather then an enchanter <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> being the main slower for a group would be awesome! And I think mages would be able to take alot more difficult mobs with a tactic like this (Proably could solo in Fire a ~bit~ more effectivly, chain casting these on a mob?) 
<br />

<br />
Would increase magician desireability alot more, and I think the potential for Magician Only groups to increase drastically. 
<br />

<br />
I think the biggest problem you'll run into is, you're giving a class an entirely new ability it never had before. Alot of people will see this as over balancing. A magician is able to control slow - so, I think a slightly altered solution would be to summon said pet, but rather then proccing slow, it would have a Slow Shield on it. 
<br />

<br />
Much like Damage Shield, which causes damage to whatever hits it, this mob would have a Slow Shield, so that the mob has to be hitting it to be slowed. 
<br />

<br />
I don't think designers will much like the idea of a magician controlling what gets slowed, just by /pet attack'ing it, but I don't think they'd be opposed to the mob being slowed ONLY if it hit the pet. 
<br />

<br />
Same idea you have, a magicians pet being able to offtank, but then it doesn't allow magicians to be a slower for a group which, while it would be AWESOME, isn't practical. 
<br />

<br />
Kapaal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
