				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">well I dont' think pets are really meant to tank GoD mobs to be honest.  giving pets more hps isn't really a fix though.  I can already solo dragons out in WW (or for an easier time, have a cleric buff and CH my pet) with airpet.
<br />

<br />
the problem is people think our pets are supposed to be able to tank everything.  thats just not going to happen.  our pets are supposed to be dps and yeah, brief backup tanks if needed.  why i'm suggesting something new is to help offtank when the situation calls.  but just because you think our pets should be able to offtank everything doesn't mean that is going to happen.
<br />

<br />
my virtue buffed airpet tanked an unslowed militis in BoT for quite a few rounds and got a quick heal from the cleric (yes i was 2boxing the cleric so i knew to heal the pet) and when it got slowed, my pet offtanked it WITHOUT ANOTHER HEAL until we killed the other add.
<br />

<br />
65 earth pet has more HPS than airpet so I would guess that you are exaggerating when you say its getting one rounded unless you are putting it up against mobs that are quadding for 1k.
<br />

<br />
air and earth pets are not wussies but yeah if they fight something unslowed, they fall fast, same as any other tank.
<br />

<br />
I'm not suggesting this is the end all solution to mages, because this isn't.  It does not address DPS problems on raids at all.  This is more of a 'hey I don't have to sit lfg for 4 hours anymore' fix.
<br />

<br />
Now the proc casting swarm pets is a pretty nifty idea.  A nice way to increase pets DPS without having to do a lot of coding for the SoE peoples.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=182653"> Wrathen's Stuff</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
