				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">ok what about these ideas?  (only one, not all)
<br />

<br />
change this from a pet to an AA buff.  lasts 1 minute, reuse timer 1 minute.  overwrites any of the pets natural procs during that 1 min.
<br />

<br />
55% slow only on what the pet is attacking.  would not stack with any other slow.
<br />

<br />
55% damage decrease.  incoming hits do 55% less damage for the mob our pet is tanking.  this would be more like a calliv on our pet so that it only takes 45% of incoming damage.  does not stack with slow (not sure how the coding on this would work).
<br />

<br />
55% avoidance buff.  pet would avoid 55% of incoming attacks on mob it is tanking or mob would miss 55% more of the time while it has this proc on it.  does not stack with slow
<br />

<br />
i'm not sure how you can get a 'damage shield' on a pet to read if the mob is slowed or not, so I'm not sure if something can be coded this way.  but they can be done as procs on the mob for sure.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=182653"> Wrathen's Stuff</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
